6) Pilot Deliverables (What “Done” Looks Like)
Within the pilot window, deliver:
2–3 UI prototypes demonstrating:
staff list scoped by manager hierarchy
equipment list per staff member
manager action to mark “collected/received”
Initial database schema for AD/Entra user data + collection logging + close out
Notification flow when an item is marked collected (Email/Teams/webhook)
Integration plan and initial wiring to ref tab API (live once env vars are available)

7) Implementation Plan (Pilot)
Phase 1 — UI Prototypes (Front-end first)
Build 2–3 prototype variants:
Table-first dashboard (fast scanning)
Staff card layout (people-centric)
Asset-centric list (return logistics-centric)
Use dummy data to validate UX and flows
Phase 2 — Data Wiring
Add DB schema + seed/sync for AD user/manager mapping
Add ref tab integration (proxy or direct)
Replace dummy equipment data with live API responses
Phase 3 — Logging + Alerts
Implement “mark collected” action and persistence
Trigger IT notifications
Add “close out” workflow for IT

8) Assumptions and Constraints
AD/Entra manager field is sufficiently populated to construct a hierarchy.
A stable identifier exists to match user records to equipment assignments (employee ID / UPN / email).
ref tab API provides required equipment assignment fields (asset tag/serial, assigned user, status).
Deployment environment supports env vars and outbound notification channel.

9) Risks and Mitigations
Incomplete manager field mapping → provide fallback rules (direct reports only; manual overrides later)
Identifier mismatches (AD vs ref tab) → define a canonical join key early and validate with sample data
API rate limits / latency → cache equipment assignments in DB if needed
Notification reliability → start with a simple, robust channel; add richer workflows later

